  "enhanced_information": "Propylthiouracil is the preferred treatment for hyperthyroidism in the first trimester of pregnancy due to its lower risk of teratogenic effects compared to Methimazole. Methimazole and its pro-drug Carbimazole, which is metabolized to Methimazole, carry higher teratogenic risks and are not recommended during the first trimester. Perchlorate, being less effective and less studied for managing hyperthyroidism in pregnancy, is not considered a first-line treatment. The evidence path confirming Propylthiouracil's use in treating hyperthyroidism supports its safety and efficacy in this specific context."
